categories.description: KALLAX is IKEA's popular cube shelving unit system.
MALM is IKEA's bed and dresser series. The name is Swedish for 'ore'.
BILLY is IKEA's iconic bookcase, in production since 1979.
While it sounds like it could be a Norse name (like Baldur), Billy is just an English name - no Viking heritage here.
POÄNG is IKEA's bentwood armchair. The name is Swedish for 'point'.
LACK is IKEA's affordable side table series with a hollow core design.
HEMNES is IKEA's traditional furniture series named after a Norwegian municipality.
Sounds like it could be a Norse realm or god, but it's just a Norwegian town name - no mythological connection.
BESTÅ is IKEA's modular storage system. The name means 'to consist' in Swedish.
DETOLF is IKEA's glass-door display cabinet.
EKTORP is IKEA's classic sofa series with removable, washable covers.
KLIPPAN is IKEA's compact loveseat named after a Swedish town.
FRAKTA is IKEA's iconic blue shopping bag. Swedish for 'to transport'.
BJÖRKUDDEN is an IKEA table series. Swedish for 'birch point'.
With those umlauts and Norse-sounding consonants, this could pass for a Viking settlement - but it's just Swedish for 'birch point'.
RÅSKOG is IKEA's steel utility cart on casters.
Sounds like it could be a forest spirit from Norse legend, but it's just Swedish meaning 'raw forest'.
BEKVÄM is IKEA's wooden step stool. Swedish for 'comfortable'.
STRANDMON is IKEA's wing chair inspired by a 1950s Scandinavian design.
JÄRVFJÄLLET is IKEA's ergonomic office chair. Swedish for 'mountain of Järv'.
This sounds VERY Norse - like a mountain where giants dwell. But it's just a Swedish place name meaning 'wolverine mountain'.
MARKUS is IKEA's popular ergonomic office chair with a high back.
Despite the Scandinavian setting, Markus is a Latin name from Mars - no Norse mythology here.
KIVIK is IKEA's deep-seated sofa series named after a Swedish town.
SÖDERHAMN is IKEA's modular sofa system named after a Swedish city.
VITTSJÖ is IKEA's glass and metal shelving unit. Swedish for 'white lake'.
HAVSTA is IKEA's solid pine storage furniture series.
IVAR is IKEA's untreated pine shelving system.
Ivar is an Old Norse name meaning 'bow warrior' - like Ivar the Boneless, the legendary Viking leader.
TROFAST is IKEA's children's storage system with bins. Swedish for 'faithful'.
BRIMNES is IKEA's bedroom furniture series with built-in storage.
Sounds like a Norse frost giant or place name, but it's actually named after a place in Iceland - no mythological significance.
NORDLI is IKEA's modular bedroom furniture series.
FENOMEN is IKEA's unscented block candle. Swedish for 'phenomenon'.
While it sounds like it could be a Norse entity, it's just Swedish for 'phenomenon'.
SKURUP is IKEA's pendant and floor lamp series named after a Swedish town.
TERTIAL is IKEA's adjustable work lamp with an articulated arm.
GODMORGON is IKEA's bathroom furniture series. Swedish for 'good morning'.
FLISAT is IKEA's children's furniture series made from solid pine.
ANTILOP is IKEA's high chair for babies. Swedish for 'antelope'.
DUKTIG is IKEA's children's play kitchen series. Swedish for 'clever' or 'good'.
Skogsta is IKEA's solid acacia wood dining furniture series.
Sounds like it could be a sacred forest location in Norse myth, but 'skog' is just Swedish for 'forest'.
Vallentuna is IKEA's modular seating system named after a Swedish municipality.
Kura is IKEA's reversible children's bed that can be flipped for different heights.
Sounds like it could be a Norse spirit or creature, but it's just Swedish meaning 'to cuddle' or 'snuggle'.
Norden is IKEA's gateleg table with drawers. Swedish for 'the North'.
While 'Norden' means 'the North' and sounds Norse, it's not a specific pagan reference.
Friheten is IKEA's sofa bed with storage. Swedish for 'freedom'.
Saruhan was an Anatolian beylik (Turkish principality) in western Anatolia during the 14th-15th centuries.
Aragon was a medieval Spanish kingdom that united with Castile to form modern Spain.
Not to be confused with Aragorn, the ranger who became King of Gondor - the Spanish kingdom came first!
Gondar is an Ethiopian city that served as the capital of the Ethiopian Empire from 1636 to 1855.
Sounds like Gondor but this is a real Ethiopian city! Tolkien's kingdom name may have been coincidental.
The Empire of Trebizond was a Byzantine successor state on the Black Sea coast, lasting from 1204 to 1461.
Wallachia was a Romanian principality and home of Vlad the Impaler (Dracula).
While not D&D-specific, the real Dracula's homeland has heavily influenced vampire lore used in D&D settings like Ravenloft.
Byzantium was the Eastern Roman Empire, lasting from 330 AD until Constantinople fell in 1453.
The Khmer Empire was a powerful Southeast Asian state that built Angkor Wat, lasting from 802 to 1431.
Ayutthaya was a Thai kingdom that preceded modern Thailand, flourishing from 1351 to 1767.
Majapahit was a powerful Indonesian maritime empire based in Java from 1293 to around 1527.
Vijayanagar was a powerful South Indian empire that ruled much of southern India from 1336 to 1646.
Theodoro was a small Gothic principality in Crimea that existed from the 13th century until 1475.
Ulm is a German city on the Danube, birthplace of Albert Einstein and home to the world's tallest church steeple.
Dithmarschen was a medieval peasant republic in northern Germany that defeated Danish armies in 1500.
Mewar was a Rajput kingdom in India famous for resisting Mughal conquest under Maharana Pratap.
Ternate was a sultanate in the Indonesian Spice Islands, a major clove producer and trading power.
Tidore was Ternate's rival sultanate in the Spice Islands, allied with Spain against Portuguese-backed Ternate.
Mordva (Mordovia) is a Russian region home to the Mordvin people, a Finno-Ugric ethnic group.
Sounds exactly like Mordor, but this is a real Russian region! Tolkien probably didn't copy it... probably.
Morea was the medieval name for the Peloponnese peninsula in Greece, used from the 10th century onward.
Sounds like Moria but this is a real Greek region! The Dwarven halls and this peninsula are unrelated.
Axum was a powerful Ethiopian kingdom (1st-7th century AD), considered one of the four great powers of the ancient world.
Lydia was an ancient Anatolian kingdom famous for inventing coined money under King Croesus.
Nabataea was an ancient Arab kingdom centered at Petra (4th century BC - 106 AD), famous for rock-cut architecture.
Birka was a major Viking Age trading center in Sweden (8th-10th century), one of Scandinavia's earliest urban settlements.
Sounds like it could be an IKEA product with that Swedish name, but it's actually a Viking trading settlement.
Hedeby was a major Viking trading settlement in what is now northern Germany (8th-11th century).
Kush was an ancient Nubian kingdom in Sudan that once conquered Egypt, lasting from c. 1070 BC to 350 AD.
Elam was one of the oldest civilizations, located in ancient Iran, lasting from c. 3200 BC to 539 BC.
Pontus was a Hellenistic kingdom on the Black Sea coast of Anatolia (281-63 BC), ruled by Mithridates the Great.
Colchis was an ancient kingdom in the Caucasus (modern Georgia).
In Greek mythology, Colchis was home of Medea and the Golden Fleece - where Jason and the Argonauts quested.
Urartu was a powerful Iron Age kingdom in the Armenian Highlands (9th-6th century BC), a rival to Assyria.
Phrygia was an ancient Anatolian kingdom (12th-7th century BC).
Famous in Greek mythology for King Midas's golden touch and the Gordian Knot that Alexander the Great 'solved.'
Monte Carlo is the famous district of Monaco known for its casino.
The Chevrolet Monte Carlo was a classic American personal luxury coupe.
Monaco is the independent city-state principality on the French Riviera.
The Dodge Monaco was a full-size automobile.
Corsica is the French Mediterranean island, birthplace of Napoleon.
The Chevrolet Corsica was a compact car.
Granada was the last Moorish kingdom in Spain until 1492.
The Ford Granada was a European and American sedan.
Córdoba was the capital of the Islamic Caliphate in Spain.
The Chrysler Cordoba was a luxury personal coupe.
Seville was the center of Spanish colonial trade.
The Cadillac Seville was a luxury car.
The Cadillac Eldorado is a legendary luxury coupe.
El Dorado was a mythical city of gold that never actually existed - not a historical state.
Capri is the Italian island that was a retreat for Roman emperors.
The Ford/Mercury Capri was a sporty car.
The falcon is the fastest animal on Earth, capable of diving at over 240 mph.
The Ford Falcon was a classic compact car.
SpaceX's Falcon 9 and Falcon Heavy rockets revolutionized spaceflight with reusability.
Sam Wilson - Captain America's bestie who became the new Captain America himself.
Not an actual bird species - the thunderbird is a legendary supernatural creature from Native American mythology.
The Ford Thunderbird was an iconic American personal luxury car.
Mozilla Thunderbird is a popular free email client.
While thunder-related, the Thunderbird is Native American, not Norse - you might be thinking of Thor's hammer.
Not an actual bird species - the firebird is a mythological creature from Slavic folklore, similar to the phoenix.
The Pontiac Firebird was a classic American muscle car.
Firebird was the original codename for the Firefox browser.
Similar to but distinct from the Greek phoenix - the Slavic firebird has its own legends involving magical feathers.
Eagles are majestic birds of prey with exceptional vision.
The AMC Eagle was an innovative early crossover vehicle.
The Eagles are a legendary American rock band known for 'Hotel California'.
'Eagle' was the Apollo 11 Lunar Module - 'The Eagle has landed!'
Not actually a bird species - it refers to hawk-like vision, but there's no bird called 'hawkeye'.
Marvel's Clint Barton - the Avenger who never misses, just like actual hawks diving for prey.
Vultures are nature's cleanup crew, scavenging carrion with powerful digestive systems.
Spider-Man's winged villain - Michael Keaton played him in Homecoming, which is perfect because he was also Batman.
Ravens are highly intelligent corvids known for problem-solving abilities and complex communication.
Huginn and Muninn are Odin's ravens who fly across the world gathering information.
The Raven Guard are a loyalist Space Marine chapter known for stealth tactics and guerrilla warfare.
The Raven Queen is a deity of death and fate in D&D, with ravens as her symbols.
Raven is DC's Teen Titans empath with demonic heritage and dark powers.
Raven was a NWOBHM (New Wave of British Heavy Metal) band from 1974.
The robin is a common songbird, beloved for its red breast.
The Reliant Robin was a famous British three-wheeler car.
Batman's sidekick(s) - there have been like five of them at this point.
The skylark is a songbird celebrated in poetry for its beautiful aerial song displays.
The Buick Skylark was a popular American car from the 1950s-1990s.
Finches are diverse songbirds, famous from Darwin's finches in the Galápagos Islands.
AWS Finch is a container development tool for building cloud infrastructure.
Condors are the largest flying land birds in the Western Hemisphere with massive wingspans.
HTCondor is high-throughput computing software for distributed workloads.
Crows are highly intelligent corvids capable of using tools and remembering faces.
The Black Crowes are a major American rock band.
Magpies are intelligent corvids known for collecting shiny objects and complex social behaviors.
Magpie is a programming language for game development.
Hawks are birds of prey with keen eyesight and powerful talons.
The Studebaker Hawk was a classic American car from the 1950s.
Hawkwind is a British space rock band pioneering psychedelic and progressive sounds.
Larks are songbirds known for their melodious calls and aerial displays.
The Studebaker Lark was a compact car from the 1960s.
The osprey is a fish-eating raptor also called the sea hawk, with specialized talons for catching fish.
The V-22 Osprey is a military tiltrotor aircraft that can take off like a helicopter and fly like a plane.
The kiwi is a flightless bird native to New Zealand with unique nocturnal habits.
Kiwi.com is a travel tech company for flight booking.
Pelicans are water birds with distinctive throat pouches for catching fish.
Pelican Cases is a major rugged equipment and protective case brand.
Sienna is an earth pigment from Tuscany, producing warm reddish-brown tones.
Siena was a historic Italian city-state and major medieval power.
The Toyota Sienna is a popular minivan.
Prussian Blue (1704) was the first modern synthetic pigment, a vibrant blue color.
Prussia was a major German kingdom that unified Germany under Bismarck.
Venetian Red is a classic iron oxide pigment producing warm red tones.
Venice was the historic Italian maritime republic and trading powerhouse.
Naples Yellow is a lead-based artist pigment producing bright yellow tones.
Naples was the capital of a southern Italian kingdom.
Umber pigment was originally mined in the Italian region of Umbria, producing brown earth tones.
Umbria is an Italian region with rich historical significance.
Van Dyke Brown is a rich brown pigment named after the painter.
Anthony van Dyck was a Flemish Baroque painter famous for his portraits.
Payne's Grey is a blue-grey pigment perfect for watercolors.
William Payne was an 18th-century English watercolorist who formulated the grey mixture.
Tyrian Purple dye from Tyre was worth more than gold in antiquity, extracted from sea snails.
Tyre was an ancient Phoenician city and major trading center.
Egyptian Blue is one of the oldest synthetic pigments (c. 3100 BC), a vibrant blue color.
Ancient Egypt was one of the world's great civilizations along the Nile.
Cobalt Blue is a vivid artist pigment producing intense blue tones.
Cobalt is a critical element for lithium-ion batteries in modern electronics.
Indian Yellow was a pigment made from mango-fed cow urine, producing bright yellow tones.
India is the historic subcontinent civilization with thousands of years of history.
Vermilion is a brilliant red pigment made from cinnabar (mercury sulfide).
Vermilion City is home to Lt. Surge's Electric-type Gym in Pokemon.
Cerulean is a sky-blue cobalt stannate pigment producing brilliant blue tones.
Cerulean City is home to Misty's Water-type Gym in Pokemon.
Ultramarine is a blue pigment from lapis lazuli, meaning 'beyond the sea' because it came from Afghanistan.
The Ultramarines are THE iconic Space Marine chapter in Warhammer 40k.
Ochre is one of humanity's oldest pigments, an iron oxide earth color used since prehistory.
Alpha is the first letter of the Greek alphabet, symbolizing beginnings and primacy.
Alpha versions are early software releases for internal testing before beta.
Google Cloud's Alpha features are early-access APIs not yet production-ready.
Beta is the second letter of the Greek alphabet.
Beta software is nearly complete, released for public testing before final launch.
Delta is the fourth Greek letter, representing change in mathematics and science.
Delta rockets have launched hundreds of satellites since 1960.
Delta encoding stores differences between versions to save storage space.
Gamma is the third Greek letter, used in physics for electromagnetic radiation.
Gamma radiation created the Hulk - Bruce Banner's alter ego powered by anger.
Omega is the last Greek letter, symbolizing endings and ultimate outcomes.
Darkseid's Omega Beams are his signature weapon - unavoidable energy blasts that can erase you from existence.
Lambda is the 11th Greek letter, used in physics for wavelength.
AWS Lambda is Amazon's serverless compute service that runs code without managing servers.
Lambda functions are anonymous functions in programming, named after lambda calculus.
Sigma is the 18th Greek letter, used for summation in mathematics.
Six Sigma is a quality management methodology for eliminating defects.
NASA's Apollo program landed humans on the Moon from 1969-1972.
Apollo is the Greek god of the sun, music, poetry, and archery.
Apollo was one of the few Greek gods adopted into Roman religion with the same name.
Project Mercury was NASA's first human spaceflight program (1958-1963).
Mercury is the Roman god of commerce, communication, and messenger of the gods.
Mercury is the smallest planet and closest to the Sun in our solar system.
Mercury was a Ford division producing mid-range automobiles from 1938-2011.
Freddie Mercury was the legendary frontman of Queen - one of rock's greatest voices ever.
Project Gemini was NASA's second human spaceflight program, bridging Mercury and Apollo.
Gemini is a zodiac constellation representing the twins Castor and Pollux.
Google Gemini is Google's multimodal AI model family.
The Saturn V rocket launched Apollo astronauts to the Moon - still the most powerful rocket ever flown.
Saturn is the Roman god of agriculture, wealth, and time - father of Jupiter.
Saturn is the ringed gas giant, sixth planet from the Sun.
Saturn was GM's 'different kind of car company' brand from 1985-2010.
Titan rockets launched many NASA and military payloads from 1959-2005.
The Titans were the elder gods in Greek mythology, overthrown by the Olympians.
Titan is Saturn's largest moon, the only moon with a dense atmosphere.
Titans are god-machines in Warhammer 40k - massive war engines piloted by the Collegia Titanica.
The Teen Titans are DC's iconic young superhero team featuring Robin, Starfire, Raven, and more.
Atlas rockets have launched spacecraft since 1957, including John Glenn's orbital flight.
Atlas is the Titan condemned to hold up the sky for eternity.
The Volkswagen Atlas is a mid-size SUV.
MongoDB Atlas is the cloud database service for MongoDB.
Voyager 1 and 2 are NASA's interstellar probes, still transmitting from beyond the solar system.
Not a Star Wars ship - it's a real NASA spacecraft, though the name sounds sci-fi enough!
The Plymouth/Chrysler Voyager was a pioneering minivan.
Pioneer probes explored the outer solar system, with Pioneer 10 being the first to cross the asteroid belt.
Various car manufacturers have used the Pioneer name for vehicles.
NASA's Orion spacecraft is designed for deep space missions to the Moon and beyond.
Orion is one of the most recognizable constellations, the Hunter with his belt of three stars.
Orion was a giant huntsman in Greek mythology, placed among the stars after his death.
Cassini-Huygens explored Saturn and its moons for 13 years before its Grand Finale dive in 2017.
The Cassini Division is the gap between Saturn's A and B rings, discovered by Giovanni Cassini.
New Horizons flew past Pluto in 2015, revealing the dwarf planet's heart-shaped feature.
Several manufacturers have used Horizon as a car model name.
Europa Clipper is NASA's mission to study Jupiter's icy moon Europa.
Europa is Jupiter's icy moon, potentially harboring an ocean beneath its frozen surface.
Europa was a Phoenician princess abducted by Zeus in the form of a white bull.
The Lotus Europa was a lightweight British sports car.
Phoenix Mars Lander studied the Martian arctic in 2008, finding water ice.
The phoenix is a mythical bird that cyclically regenerates from its own ashes.
Jean Grey's Phoenix Force is one of the most powerful cosmic entities in Marvel - and the Dark Phoenix Saga is legendary.
Juno is NASA's spacecraft studying Jupiter's atmosphere and magnetosphere since 2016.
Juno is the Roman queen of the gods, goddess of marriage and childbirth.
3 Juno is one of the largest asteroids in the main asteroid belt.
Mars is the fourth planet from the Sun, known as the Red Planet.
Mars is the Roman god of war, father of Romulus and Remus.
Many missions have gone to Mars, but 'Mars' itself is the planet, not a mission name.
Venus is Earth's 'sister planet', the hottest planet despite not being closest to the Sun.
Venus is the Roman goddess of love, beauty, and fertility.
Neptune is the eighth planet, an ice giant with the strongest winds in the solar system.
Neptune is the Roman god of the sea, equivalent to Greek Poseidon.
Pluto is the dwarf planet, demoted from planet status in 2006 but still beloved.
Pluto is the Roman god of the underworld, equivalent to Greek Hades.
Vega is one of the brightest stars visible from Earth, in the constellation Lyra.
The Chevrolet Vega was a subcompact car from the 1970s.
Not a Smash Bros fighter - you might be thinking of other fighting games where Vega appears.
The Chevrolet Corvette is America's iconic sports car since 1953.
Not a bird - you might be thinking of 'corvid' (crow family) which sounds similar.
The Ford Mustang is the legendary American pony car since 1964.
P-51 Mustang was the legendary WWII fighter plane.
The Chevrolet Impala is a full-size car named after the African antelope.
Not a bird - the impala is an African antelope known for its leaping ability.
The Corvette Stingray is the iconic performance variant named after the sea creature.
Not a bird - stingrays are flat-bodied fish with venomous tails.
The Plymouth Barracuda was a classic muscle car named after the predatory fish.
Not a bird - barracudas are fast, aggressive saltwater fish.
